text.__SUMMARY__:
Shorea kudatensis (also called Seraya Kuning Kudat) is a species of plant in the Dipterocarpaceae family. It is endemic the island of Borneo, in the low coastal hill in the north and west of Malaysian Sabah.The species has lost approximately 90% of its natural habitat and is currently listed as critically endangered on the IUCN Red List.
